  CSS-7 Basic of CSS Selector

<style>
  saw {
    color:gray
  }
</style>

It doesn't work . cuz this code is all saw could be Selector on this web page.
So you would focus ' class="saw" '  not a all saw. Then you put '.'in front of 'saw'
then it will point out 'class="saw" '


class="saw"







